O that thou wert as my brother that sucked the brests of my mother , when I should find thee without , I would kisse thee , yet I should not be despised .
I would leade thee , and bring thee into my mothers house , who would instruct me : I would cause thee to drinke of spiced wine , of the iuice of my pomegranate .
His left hand should be vnder my head , and his right hand should embrace me .
I charge you , O daughters of Ierusalem , that ye stirre not vp , nor awake my loue vntill he please .
